Peru Stocks: Candente, Maple, Relapasa, Southern Copper, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-07T18:13:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/peru-stocks-candente-maple-relapasa-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:19 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index gained 0.8 percent to 20,087.85. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 0.3 percent to 2,660.32.  Copper and zinc miners gained after metals surged in New
York and  London , said Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based
Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, jumped 5.1 percent to 4 soles.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO) 
, Peru’s biggest copper producer, rose 3.8 percent to
$32.80.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, advanced 3.5 percent to $1.17. Sociedad Minera Cerro
Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold
Inc., climbed 3.1 percent to $39.30.  Fuel refiners rebounded after crude futures in New York
advanced.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA known as Relapasa, rose 3.7 percent to 84
centimos.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, gained 0.9 percent to $1.08.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
